Description: Papyrus. Demotic account of one column of 13+x lines on the recto. Verso: blank. The papyrus is torn on both sides and at the bottom, but there is a top margin of c. 1.5 cm. Although torn on the right, the beginning of each line of the column is preserved.
Curator's comments: The papyrus contains the beginnings of one column of an account, but the ends of the lines are lost. It begins with a date, regnal-year 9, first month of Peret (?). There is then a space and another date, 'first month of Peret to month 4' (the name of the season is rubbed off). In line 7 another section begins with 'third month of Shemu'. There is a space before the last preserved line, which begins with 'Remainder of that which is owing (?)'.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380990) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380990)
